This product includes software developed by third parties. A per-package
manifest with aggregated license texts is maintained in THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.md
at the repository root. A reproducible audit — including license expression
sources, verification method, and reaffirmation cadence — is kept in
docs/licensing-audit.md.

The **authoritative machine-readable dependency inventory** for each release
is the Software Bill of Materials (SBOM) described in docs/security/sbom.md
(CycloneDX 1.5 JSON, published alongside release artifacts). THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.md
and this NOTICE file are the **human-readable attribution copy** derived from
that inventory; where the two ever disagree on a resolved version, the SBOM
wins. For MIT / Apache-2.0 §4(d) / BSD-3-Clause attribution purposes, what
matters is that the copyright holder for each package is named correctly —
and those do not drift with version bumps.

As of v2.0.0, the resolved dependency graph uses these licenses:

    MIT             - the majority of Microsoft / Azure / .NET / OpenAI /
                      dotenv.net packages. Compatible with this project's MIT.
    Apache-2.0      - the OpenTelemetry packages (new in v2). Compatible with
                      MIT. The upstream opentelemetry-dotnet repository carries
                      no NOTICE file at version 1.15.2, so Apache-2.0 section
                      4(d) imposes no inherited notice text on this project.
    BSD-3-Clause    - Google.Protobuf, pulled transitively by the OpenTelemetry
                      OTLP exporter. Compatible with MIT. The no-endorsement
                      clause is honored by this project's trademark policy.

No copyleft licenses (GPL / LGPL / AGPL / MPL / SSPL / EPL / CDDL / CC-NC)
are present in the v2.0.0 dependency graph. See docs/licensing-audit.md
for the complete per-package table and verification record.

